    "article_content": "Nestlé India Limited Board Meeting scheduled for April 21, 2026 to consider audited financial results for FY26 under Regulation 29\nNestlé India Limited announced a board meeting on April 21, 2026, to review standalone and consolidated audited financial results for the financial year ending March 31, 2026. The company has implemented a trading window closure from April 1-23, 2026, following SEBI insider trading regulations, with formal communication made under Regulation 29 of SEBI listing requirements.\n*this image is generated using AI for illustrative purposes only.\nNestlé India Limited has officially announced that its Board of Directors will convene on April 21, 2026, to consider the audited financial results for the financial year ending March 31, 2026. The announcement was made through a formal communication to stock exchanges on March 24, 2026, under Regulation 29 of the SEBI (Listing Obligations and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations, 2015.\nBoard Meeting Details\nThe company has scheduled the board meeting for Tuesday, April 21, 2026, specifically to review both standalone and consolidated audited financial results for FY26. This meeting represents a crucial milestone in the company's annual financial reporting cycle.\nTrading Window Closure\nIn compliance with SEBI regulations, Nestlé India has announced the closure of its trading window from April 1, 2026, to April 23, 2026 (both days inclusive). This closure is implemented in accordance with the SEBI (Prohibition of Insider Trading) Regulations, 2015.\nRegulatory Compliance and Communication\nThe announcement has been made under Regulation 29 of the SEBI (Listing Obligations and Disclosure Requirements) Regulations, 2015. The company has communicated this information to both BSE Limited (Scrip Code: 500790) and National Stock Exchange of India Limited (Symbol: NESTLEIND).\nThe formal communication was signed by Pramod Kumar Rai, Company Secretary and Compliance Officer, with digital signature authentication dated March 24, 2026. The company has uploaded this intimation on its official website at www.nestle.in for stakeholder reference.\nCompany Information\nNestlé India Limited operates from its corporate office at Nestlé House, Jacaranda Marg, 'M' Block, DLF City, Phase – II, Gurugram – 122002, Haryana. The company maintains investor communications through investor@in.nestle.com and provides comprehensive information on its website www.nestle.in .\nHistorical Stock Returns for Nestle\nWhat key performance metrics and growth indicators should investors watch for in Nestlé India's FY26 results given the current FMCG market conditions?\nHow might Nestlé India's FY26 financial performance influence its dividend policy and capital allocation strategy for the upcoming fiscal year?\nWill Nestlé India announce any major expansion plans or new product launches during the April 21st board meeting alongside the financial results?",
